docs.lead_paragraph: PUNTA DEL ESTE, Uruguay --One of South America's riddles focuses on the Rio de la Plata, or Silver River, where Argentina and Uruguay, the continent's most puzzling failures, meet. These are highly endowed lands with minimal race problems and immensely civilized traditions. Both possess the infrastructure of modernity: good communications, splendid cities, fine universities, hospitals, resorts. Yet each in its own way seems intent on messing up its prospects.
